OL,3,CLast remaining Channel Island Normandy
OL,4,CVeteran shares his memories
OL,6,F"The noise of the tanks, and on the
OL,7,Ffront, there were revolving cylinders,
OL,8,Fattached to chains, so as the chains
OL,9,Fhit the ground and explode the bombs"
OL,11,FThe one-hundred-year-old does not
OL,12,Fbelieve he is a hero, he says: "I
OL,13,Fdidn't do anything brave or anything
OL,14,Flike that."
OL,16,F"Oh me a hero, no no, I didn't do
OL,17,Fanything spectacular, I just made up a
OL,18,Fnumber."
